<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1161,1447]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
1. Ventral facial emargination very shallowly arched, almost flat (Fig. 7); facial ratio 0.50; dorsal facial seta well developed; scutellar base with a dentate, sharp, short projection laterally (Cuba).............................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson" authorityName="Cresson. A" authorityYear="1922" box="[1243,1435,1190,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Peltopsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarzi">
<emphasis box="[1243,1351,1190,1211]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">P. schwarzi</emphasis>
Cresson
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1161,1447]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
- Ventral facial emargination conspicuously arched (
<figureCitation box="[709,800,1220,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1768,1791]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,463,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,447,1747]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6. Adult of Peltopsilopa Hendel. (1 ‒ 3) P. acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (1) Head, frontal view. (2) Body, dorsal view. (3) Same, lateral view. (4 ‒ 6) P. anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (4) Head, frontal view. (5) Body, dorsal view. (6) Same, lateral view. (7 ‒ 9) P. schwarzi Cresson (Cuba. Cienfuegos: Cayamas (22 ° 14 ' N, 80 ° 48 ' W; 26 m )). (7) Head, frontal view. (8) Body, dorsal view. (9) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054068/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Figs. 1, 4</figureCitation>
); facial ratio 0.61‒0.63; dorsal facial seta more weakly developed; scutellar base lacking a dentate, sharp, short projection laterally (mainland Neotropics).............................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1161,1447]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
2. Presurstylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[508,580,1278,1299]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 ‒ 33" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[191,1333,200,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[176,1349,193,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30 ‒ 33. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (30) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (31) Same, lateral view. (32) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (33) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054076/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) elongate (length ca. 4.5X width), slender, parallel sided, apex shallowly rounded and drawn to a anteroventral point; postsurstylus in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[814,884,1308,1329]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 ‒ 44" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1839,1862]" captionTargetBox="[228,1362,199,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[215,1372,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 34 ‒ 44. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (34) Aedeagus, ventral view. (35) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (36) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (37) Hypandrium, ventral view. (38) Same, lateral view. (39) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (40) Same, lateral view. (41) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (42) Pregonite, ventral view. (43) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (44) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054078/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
) with apex digitiform, not angulate................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Karsch)" authorityName="Savaris &amp; Marinoni &amp; Mathis" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Savaris &amp; Marinoni &amp; Mathis" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[1183,1436,1337,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Peltopsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisotomoides">
<emphasis box="[1183,1346,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">P. anisotomoides</emphasis>
(Karsch)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1161,1447]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
- Presurstylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[506,578,1366,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) shorter and more robust (length no more than 
<date box="[1050,1079,1366,1387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">3X</date>
width), pedunculated with posterior margin conspicuously emarginate, widened at base and apex; postsurstylus in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1109,1179,1396,1417]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) with apical portion angulate, with a short extension at 90°............................................................... 
